ype\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary report.\\n\\n## Summary Report: Background LLM-Based Trail Title/Description Generation\\n\\nBased on thorough exploration of the codebase, here are my findings across the five key areas:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **1. Summarize Package API (`cmd/entire/cli/summarize/`)**\\n\\n**Key Components:**\\n\\n- **`summarize.go`** - Main entry points:\\n  - `GenerateFromTranscript(ctx, transcriptBytes, filesTouched, agentType, generator) (*checkpoint.Summary, error)` - High-level API\\n  - `Input` struct: `{Transcript []Entry, FilesTouched []string}`\\n  - `Generator` interface: `Generate(ctx context.Context, input Input) (*checkpoint.Summary, error)`\\n  - `Entry` struct: `{Type, Content, ToolName, ToolDetail}`\\n\\n- **`claude.go`** - `ClaudeGenerator` implementation:\\n  - Invokes Claude CLI via `exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"claude\\\", \\\"--print\\\", \\\"--output-format\\\", \\\"json\\\", \\\"--model\\\", model)`\\n  - Passes transcript via stdin, captures stdout as JSON\\n  - Response: `{\\\"result\\\": \\\"<json-string>\\\"}`\\n  - Parses response into `checkpoint.Summary` struct\\n  - **Isolation:** Runs in `os.TempDir()`, strips all `GIT_*` env vars to prevent recursive hook triggering\\n  - **Model:** Defaults to `\\\"sonnet\\\"` (good cost/quality ratio)\\n\\n- **`checkpoint.Summary` struct:**\\n  ```go\\n  type Summary struct {\\n    Intent     string            // What user wanted to accomplish (1-2 sentences)\\n    Outcome    string            // What was achieved (1-2 sentences)\\n    Learnings  LearningsSummary  // Categorized findings {Repo, Code, Workflow arrays}\\n    Friction   []string          // Problems/blockers encountered\\n    OpenItems  []string          // Tech debt, unfinished work\\n  }\\n  ```\\n\\n**Usage Pattern:**\\n```go\\ninput := summarize.Input{\\n  Transcript: condensedLines,\\n  FilesTouched: files,\\n}\\nsummary, err := generator.Generate(ctx, input) // Returns *checkpoint.Summary\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **2. Goroutine & Background Patterns in Codebase**\\n\\n**Very Limited Existing Use:**\\n- **Only 1 file** uses goroutines: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap_test.go` (testing only, no production goroutines)\\n- **No `sync.WaitGroup` usage** anywhere in strategy or cli packages\\n- **No channel usage** for coordination\\n\\n**Mutex Usage (Read-Write Locking):**\\n- `paths/paths.go`: `repoRootMu sync.RWMutex` for caching repo root (prevents race on first lookup)\\n- `agent/registry.go`: `registryMu sync.RWMutex` for agent registry (factory pattern)\\n\\n**Implication:** The codebase is **synchronous throughout**. Lifecycle events are dispatched sequentially by hooks. Background generation would be a NEW pattern.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **3. `checkpoint.Summary` Struct & Reusability**\\n\\n**Structure:**\\n- 5 fields: `Intent`, `Outcome`, `Learnings` (with 3 arrays), `Friction`, `OpenItems`\\n- JSON marshaled format\\n- Designed for full session summarization (not partial)\\n\\n**Trail Metadata Needs:**\\n```go\\ntype trail.Metadata struct {\\n  TrailID     trail.ID    // 12-hex-char ID\\n  Branch      string      \\n  Base        string\\n  Title       string      // User/generated title (80 char max per existing code)\\n  Description string      // Full description\\n  Status      trail.Status\\n  Author      string\\n  Assignees   []string\\n  Labels      []string\\n  CreatedAt   time.Time\\n  UpdatedAt   time.Time\\n  MergedAt    *time.Time\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Reusability Assessment:**\\n- ✅ **Yes, largely reusable** - Both need condensed transcript parsing\\n- ✅ Can share `summarize.Input` struct and transcript condensation logic\\n- ❌ **But** summary generation is overkill for titles - just need first line of prompt or a simple extract\\n- ⚠️ **Trail doesn't need full `checkpoint.Summary`** - just title + optional description\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Create a **lighter generation path** (`GenerateTrailTitle` / `GenerateTrailDescription`) that:\\n- Takes only transcript + prompt\\n- Calls Claude with simpler prompt (extract 1-2 sentences for title)\\n- Returns just `{title, description}` (not full Summary struct)\\n- Reuses transcript condensation logic from `summarize` but not full LLM prompt\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **4. `AutoCreateTrailOnTurnStart` End-to-End Flow**\\n\\n**Current Implementation** (in `lifecycle.go:768-791`):\\n```go\\nfunc autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart(prompt string) {\\n  // 1. Check if trails disabled\\n  if settings.IsTrailsDisabled() { return }\\n  \\n  // 2. Check if on non-main branch\\n  isDefault, branchName, err := IsOnDefaultBranch()\\n  if err || isDefault || branchName == \\\"\\\" { return }\\n  \\n  // 3. Open repo and get base branch\\n  repo, err := strategy.OpenRepository()\\n  baseBranch := strategy.GetDefaultBranchName(repo)\\n  \\n  // 4. Create trail with title from prompt\\n  AutoCreateTrail(repo, branchName, baseBranch, prompt)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Data Available at TurnStart:**\\n- ✅ `event.Prompt` - User's initial prompt (full text)\\n- ✅ `branchName` - Current branch name\\n- ✅ `baseBranch` - Target branch for merge\\n- ✅ `event.SessionID` - Session identifier\\n- ❌ `filesTouched` - **NOT available yet** (only known after TurnEnd)\\n- ❌ Full transcript - **NOT available yet** (session just starting)\\n\\n**Current Title Generation** (`trail_cmd.go:507-520`):\\n```go\\nfunc titleFromPrompt(prompt string) string {\\n  line, _, _ := strings.Cut(prompt, \\\"\\\\n\\\")  // First line only\\n  title := strings.TrimSpace(line)\\n  if len(title) > 80 {\\n    title = title[:77] + \\\"...\\\"\\n  }\\n  return title\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Updating Trail After Creation:**\\n- ✅ **Yes, `store.Update()` exists** (in `trail/store.go:280-290`):\\n  ```go\\n  func (s *Store) Update(trailID trail.ID, updateFn func(*Metadata)) error {\\n    metadata, discussion, checkpoints, err := s.Read(trailID)\\n    if err != nil { return err }\\n    \\n    updateFn(metadata)           // Mutation function\\n    metadata.UpdatedAt = time.Now()\\n    \\n    return s.Write(metadata, discussion, checkpoints)  // Persist\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- ✅ **Can be called from hook later** to update title/description with LLM result\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **5. CRITICAL - Git Operations & Concurrency Safety 🔴**\\n\\n**Git Operations on `entire/trails` Branch:**\\n\\nThe trail store uses go-git plumbing APIs:\\n- `repo.Storer.SetReference(newRef)` - Update ref (atomic)\\n- `repo.Storer.SetEncodedObject(obj)` - Write blob (atomic)\\n- `BuildTreeFromEntries()` - Build git tree from map\\n- `CreateBlobFromContent()` - Create blob\\n\\n**Race Condition Risk - VERY HIGH:**\\n\\n1. **Where writes happen:**\\n   - `autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart()` (TurnStart hook, synchronous) → calls `store.Write()`\\n   - `appendCheckpointToTrail()` (PostCommit hook, synchronous) → calls `store.AddCheckpoint()` → calls `store.Write()`\\n   - **Proposed:** Background goroutine calling `store.Update()`\\n\\n2. **The Problem:**\\n   ```\\n   Timeline:\\n   T0: TurnStart hook → autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart() → store.Write() [creates trail, writes entire/trails commit]\\n   T1: Background goroutine starts\\n   T2: PostCommit hook → appendCheckpointToTrail() → store.Read() [reads old tree]\\n   T3: Background goroutine → store.Update() → store.Read() [reads old tree]\\n   T4: T2 writes new commit to entire/trails\\n   T5: T3 writes new commit to entire/trails (based on T2's parent, LOST T2's update)\\n   T6: Race condition - one update lost!\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Why This Is Critical:**\\n   - `store.Write()` does **read-modify-write**:\\n     ```go\\n     ref, entries, err := s.getBranchEntries()  // Read current\\n     entries[path] = updated                     // Modify\\n     newTreeHash, err := BuildTreeFromEntries()  // Build new tree\\n     commitHash, err := s.createCommit(newTreeHash, ref.Hash(), msg, ...)  // Create commit\\n     s.repo.Storer.SetReference(newRef)         // Write atomic, but...\\n     ```\\n   - Between `getBranchEntries()` and `SetReference()`, another writer can complete\\n   - go-git's `SetReference()` is atomic **per operation**, but not across the full read-modify-write cycle\\n   - The `repo.Storer` itself has **no locks** (it's not thread-safe for mixed reads/writes)\\n\\n4. **go-git Object Database Safety:**\\n   - ✅ `SetReference()` is atomic for single ref update\\n   - ✅ `SetEncodedObject()` is atomic for single blob\\n   - ❌ **NO mutual exclusion** between concurrent readers and writers to the same branch\\n   - ❌ **NO transaction semantics** across multiple git objects\\n\\n5. **Current Code Pattern - Works Because Synchronous:**\\n   ```go\\n   // manual_commit_hooks.go - appendCheckpointToTrail\\n   appendCheckpointToTrail(repo, cpID, head.Hash(), result.Prompts)  // Sync call in PostCommit\\n   \\n   // trail_cmd.go - AutoCreateTrail  \\n   AutoCreateTrail(repo, branchName, baseBranch, prompt)  // Sync call in TurnStart\\n   ```\\n   These are **both synchronous**, called from git hooks sequentially.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **DESIGN IMPLICATIONS FOR BACKGROUND GENERATION:**\\n\\n**If you use a background goroutine:**\\n\\n```go\\n// UNSAFE - Race condition risk:\\ngo func() {\\n  time.Sleep(delay)\\n  store := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n  store.Update(trailID, func(m *Metadata) {\\n    m.Title = generatedTitle\\n    m.Description = generatedDescription\\n  })\\n}()\\n```\\n\\n**Scenarios where this breaks:**\\n1. TurnStart creates trail (T0)\\n2. Background goroutine starts generating (T1)\\n3. User manually edits trail with `entire trail update` (T2) → writes to entire/trails\\n4. Background goroutine finishes → `store.Update()` reads pre-T2 state → writes, **loses manual edit** (T4)\\n\\n5. PostCommit hook appends checkpoint while background generation is in progress\\n6. Both call `store.Read()` → get same parent ref\\n7. Both call `store.Write()` → second write loses first one\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **SOLUTIONS (In Order of Recommendation):**\\n\\n**Option A: File-based Lock (Simplest, Most Reliable) ✅ RECOMMENDED**\\n```go\\nlockPath := filepath.Join(repoRoot, \\\".git\\\", \\\"entire-trail-lock\\\")\\nlock := flock.New(lockPath)\\nlock.Lock()\\ndefer lock.Unlock()\\n\\nstore.Update(trailID, updateFn)  // Now safe\\n```\\n- Ensures exclusive access to entire/trails branch\\n- Works across processes/hooks/goroutines\\n- Used throughout the codebase for session state files\\n- **Zero changes to trail store**\\n\\n**Option B: Mutex in Hook Handler**\\n- Keep background goroutine, but add mutex to `appendCheckpointToTrail`:\\n  ```go\\n  var trailMu sync.Mutex\\n  \\n  func appendCheckpointToTrail(...) {\\n    trailMu.Lock()\\n    defer trailMu.Unlock()\\n    store.AddCheckpoint(...)\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- **Problem:** Won't protect against manual `entire trail update` or other processes\\n- **Advantage:** Minimal code changes\\n\\n**Option C: Transaction-like Wrapper**\\n- Add retries with exponential backoff:\\n  ```go\\n  for attempt := 0; attempt < 3; attempt++ {\\n    oldMetadata, _, _, err := store.Read(trailID)\\n    if err != nil { return err }\\n    \\n    newMetadata := *oldMetadata\\n    updateFn(&newMetadata)\\n    \\n    // Check if nothing changed in between (optimistic locking)\\n    err = store.Update(trailID, func(m) { *m = newMetadata })\\n    if err == nil { return nil }\\n    \\n    time.Sleep(time.Duration(1<<uint(attempt)) * 100*time.Millisecond)\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- **Problem:** Still racy; doesn't actually prevent the race\\n- **Advantage:** Reduces likelihood of lost updates\\n\\n**Option D: Defer to Existing Hook Pattern (Most Conservative)**\\n- Don't use background goroutine\\n- Add title/description generation to existing `PostCommit` or `PrePush` hook\\n- Synchronous, no concurrency issues\\n- **Trade-off:** Adds latency to commit/push operations\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **SUMMARY TABLE:**\\n\\n| Area | Finding | Impact |