e/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n\\n```go\\ntype CheckpointRef struct {\\n    CheckpointID string    `json:\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"`\\n    CommitSHA    string    `json:\\\"commit_sha\\\"`\\n    CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n    Summary      string    `json:\\\"summary,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype Checkpoints struct {\\n    Checkpoints []CheckpointRef `json:\\\"checkpoints\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### A2. Update trail store to read/write checkpoints.json\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go`\\n\\n- Add `checkpointsFile = \\\"checkpoints.json\\\"` constant\\n- Update `Write()` signature: add `checkpoints *Checkpoints` parameter. When nil, write empty `{\\\"checkpoints\\\":[]}`. Write blob to `<trailPath>/checkpoints.json`\\n- Update all `Write()` callers: `trail_cmd.go:AutoCreateTrail`, `trail_cmd.go:runTrailCreate`, `store.go:Update`\\n- Update `Read()` to return `*Checkpoints` as 3rd return value\\n- Add `AddCheckpoint(trailID ID, ref CheckpointRef) error` — reads existing, prepends new ref (newest first), writes back via `Write()`\\n- Update `Update()` to preserve existing checkpoints (read them, pass through to Write)\\n\\n### A3. Link checkpoints to trails on condensation (manual-commit)\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\nAdd `Prompts []string` field to `CondenseResult` (in `manual_commit_types.go`). Populate it in `CondenseSession()` from `sessionData.Prompts`.\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\nIn `condenseAndUpdateState()`, after successful `CondenseSession()` (line 811), call:\\n```go\\nappendCheckpointToTrail(repo, result.CheckpointID, head.Hash(), result.Prompts)\\n```\\n\\nNew helper (in `manual_commit_hooks.go`):\\n```go\\nfunc appendCheckpointToTrail(repo *git.Repository, cpID id.CheckpointID, commitSHA plumbing.Hash, prompts []string) {\\n    branchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\n    if branchName == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    defaultBranch := GetDefaultBranchName(repo)\\n    if branchName == defaultBranch {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    store := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n    existing, err := store.FindByBranch(branchName)\\n    if err != nil || existing == nil {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    var summary string\\n    if len(prompts) > 0 {\\n        summary = truncateForSummary(prompts[len(prompts)-1], 200)\\n    }\\n    _ = store.AddCheckpoint(existing.TrailID, trail.CheckpointRef{\\n        CheckpointID: cpID.String(),\\n        CommitSHA:    commitSHA.String(),\\n        CreatedAt:    time.Now().UTC(),\\n        Summary:      summary,\\n    })\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### A4. Link checkpoints to trails (auto-commit)\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go`\\n\\nIn `SaveStep()`, after successful metadata commit (after line 163):\\n```go\\nappendCheckpointToTrail(repo, cpID, codeResult.CommitHash, nil)\\n// Summary: use ctx.CommitMessage since prompts aren't extracted at this point\\n```\\n\\nActually, auto-commit's `StepContext` doesn't have prompts. Use `ctx.CommitMessage` as summary, or pass nil and skip summary.\\n\\n## Part B: Semantic Trail Titles\\n\\n### B1. Pass prompt through to trail auto-creation\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`\\n\\n```go\\n// Line 149: change\\nautoCreateTrailOnTurnStart()\\n// to\\nautoCreateTrailOnTurnStart(event.Prompt)\\n```\\n\\nUpdate `autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart` signature to `(prompt string)`. Pass through:\\n```go\\nAutoCreateTrail(repo, branchName, baseBranch, prompt)\\n```\\n\\n### B2. Use prompt for trail title\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go`\\n\\nUpdate `AutoCreateTrail` to accept `prompt string`:\\n```go\\nfunc AutoCreateTrail(repo *git.Repository, branchName, baseBranch, prompt string) error {\\n    ...\\n    title := titleFromPrompt(prompt)\\n    if title == \\\"\\\" {\\n        title = trail.HumanizeBranchName(branchName)\\n    }\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd helper:\\n```go\\nfunc titleFromPrompt(prompt string) string {\\n    if prompt == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return \\\"\\\"\\n    }\\n    line, _, _ := strings.Cut(prompt, \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n    title := strings.TrimSpace(line)\\n    if len(title) > 80 {\\n        title = title[:77] + \\\"...\\\"\\n    }\\n    return title\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### B3. Update CLAUDE.md\\nDocument `checkpoints.json` format and prompt-based title generation.\\n\\n## Files Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go` | Add `CheckpointRef`, `Checkpoints` types |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go` | Write/read `checkpoints.json`, add `AddCheckpoint()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go` | Update `AutoCreateTrail` for prompt, update `Write()` calls, add `titleFromPrompt` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` | Add `Prompts` to `CondenseResult` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Populate `Prompts` in result |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Add `appendCheckpointToTrail` helper, call after condensation |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go` | Call `appendCheckpointToTrail` after save |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` | Pass `event.Prompt` to `autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart` |\\n| `CLAUDE.md` | Document changes |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"63d22d1e-140c-49e1-9895-72c90f9d4c96\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4c518c90-2f89-4485-a0fe-973834c5f56c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/dip/Repositories/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6edd18ba-782c-4019-88d9-018079feea08\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wondrous-finding-raven\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01TLynpNV85BtGxvZP663iEZ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me check the `StepContext` struct to verify what fields auto-commit has access to, and also check if there's anything else I need to know before fi