ased titles) are already implemented and passing CI. However, `titleFromPrompt()` just truncates the first line of the user's prompt, which produces mediocre titles like \\\"implement the login flow for...\\\" instead of semantic titles like \\\"User authentication login flow\\\".\\n\\nThe user wants an LLM to generate proper trail titles and descriptions from the session transcript. This should happen **at first condensation** (PostCommit), not TurnStart, because:\\n- Rich context is available (prompts + transcript + files touched)\\n- Only happens once per trail (first commit)\\n- No concurrency issues (runs synchronously in the hook process)\\n- Piggybacks on existing summarize flow\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n### C1. Add `GenerateTrailTitle` to the summarize package\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/trail_title.go` (new file)\\n\\nAdd a prompt template and generation function for trail titles:\\n\\n```go\\nconst trailTitlePromptTemplate = `Analyze this development session transcript and generate a concise title and description for a code review / pull request.\\n\\n<transcript>\\n%s\\n</transcript>\\n\\nReturn a JSON object with this exact structure:\\n{\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Short imperative title (max 80 chars, e.g. 'Add user authentication login flow')\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"1-3 sentence description of what was accomplished and why\\\"\\n}\\n\\nGuidelines:\\n- Title should be imperative mood, like a commit message subject\\n- Title should capture the core intent, not implementation details\\n- Description should explain the \\\"what\\\" and \\\"why\\\", not the \\\"how\\\"\\n- Be concise and specific\\n- Return ONLY the JSON object, no markdown formatting`\\n\\ntype TrailTitleResult struct {\\n    Title       string `json:\\\"title\\\"`\\n    Description string `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n}\\n\\nfunc GenerateTrailTitle(ctx context.Context, transcriptBytes []byte, filesTouched []string, agentType agent.AgentType) (*TrailTitleResult, error)\\n```\