nes:\\n- Title: imperative mood, captures core intent (e.g. \\\"Add user authentication flow\\\")\\n- Description: explain \\\"what\\\" and \\\"why\\\", not \\\"how\\\"\\n- Return ONLY the JSON object`\\n\\ntype TrailTitleResult struct {\\n    Title       string `json:\\\"title\\\"`\\n    Description string `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n}\\n\\nfunc GenerateTrailTitle(ctx context.Context, transcriptBytes []byte, filesTouched []string, agentType agent.AgentType) (*TrailTitleResult, error) {\\n    // Build condensed transcript (reuse existing BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes + FormatCondensedTranscript)\\n    // Invoke Claude CLI with haiku model (reuse stripGitEnv, extractJSONFromMarkdown patterns from claude.go)\\n    // Parse JSON response into TrailTitleResult\\n}\\n```\\n\\nKey reuse:\\n- `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes()` + `FormatCondensedTranscript()` for transcript formatting\\n- `stripGitEnv()` and `extractJSONFromMarkdown()` from `claude.go`\\n- Same subprocess pattern: `claude --print --output-format json --model haiku --setting-sources \\\"\\\"`\\n\\n### C2. Add `Transcript` field to `CondenseResult`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go`\\n\\n```go\\ntype CondenseResult struct {\\n    ...existing fields...\\n    Transcript []byte   // Raw transcript bytes for downstream consumers\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\nIn `CondenseSession()` return block (~line 250), add:\\n```go\\nTranscript: sessionData.Transcript,\\n```\\n\\n### C3. Add `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript` helper\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo *git.Repository, branchName string, transcript []byte, filesTouched []string, agentType agent.AgentType) {\\n    if !settings.IsSummarizeEnabled() {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    store := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n    existing, err := store.FindByBranch(branchName)\\n    if err != nil || existing == nil {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    // Only generate once: skip if description already set\\n    if existing.Description != \\\"\\\" {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    ctx := context.Background()\\n    result, err := summarize.GenerateTrailTitle(ctx, transcript, filesTouched, agentType)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        logging.Debug(ctx, \\\"trail title generation failed\\\", slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()))\\n        return\\n    }\\n    //nolint:errcheck // best-effort: trail title generation is non-critical\\n    store.Update(existing.TrailID, func(m *trail.Metadata) {\\n        if result.Title != \\\"\\\" {\\n            m.Title = result.Title\\n        }\\n        if result.Description != \\\"\\\" {\\n            m.Description = result.Description\\n        }\\n    })\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### C4. Wire into `condenseAndUpdateState` (manual-commit)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\nIn `condenseAndUpdateState()`, after the existing `appendCheckpointToTrail()` call (~line 825):\\n\\n```go\\n// Generate trail title/description from transcript (best-effort, first condensation only)\\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\nif branchName != \\\"\\\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) {\\n    generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo, branchName, result.Transcript, result.FilesTouched, state.AgentType)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### C5. Wire into `SaveStep` (auto-commit)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go`\\n\\nIn `SaveStep()`, after the existing `appendCheckpointToTrail()` call (~line 166):\\n\\n```go\\n// Generate trail title/description (best-effort, first condensation only)\\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\nif branchName != \\\"\\\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) && ctx.TranscriptPath != \\\"\\\" {\\n    if transcriptData, readErr := os.ReadFile(ctx.TranscriptPath); readErr == nil {\\n        filesTouched := mergeFilesTouched(nil, ctx.ModifiedFiles, ctx.NewFiles, ctx.DeletedFiles)\\n        generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo, branchName, transcriptData, filesTouched, ctx.AgentType)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Files Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/trail_title.go` | **New**: `GenerateTrailTitle()`, prompt template, `TrailTitleResult` type |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` | Add `Transcript []byte` to `CondenseResult` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Populate `Transcript` in `CondenseResult` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Add `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()`, wire after condensation |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go` | Wire `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()` after save |\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **Haiku model** — trail titles are simple; haiku is fast (~1-2s) and cheap\\n2. **One-time gate** — `Description != \\\"\\\"` ensures LLM is only called on first condensation per trail\\n3. **Settings gate** — reuses `settings.IsSummarizeEnabled()`; no new setting\\n4. **Best-effort** — all errors logged and swallowed; non-critical metadata\\n5. **Synchronous** — runs in PostCommit hook; no goroutines, no race conditions\\n6. **Reuses transcript infrastructure** — `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes` + `FormatCondensedTranscript`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nManual test:\\n1. Create a branch, enable entire\\n2. Run an agent session, make a commit\\n3. Check `entire trail` output — should show LLM-generated title and description\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"9d168637-c58e-4a59-9415-47b077e938c3\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a9f8c663-877a-4e5c-92ed-bab5b1fbb0c9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/dip/Repositories/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6edd18ba-782c-4019-88d9-018079feea08\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wondrous-finding-raven\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01